Would we consider changing the rendering behavior for a JavaScript object when `Content-Type` has been explicitly set to something other than `*/json`?

Consider the following example:

``` javascript
app.post('/xml', function(request, response) {
    // .toString() on this object returns an XML representation of this object
    var reply = new XmlRenderingThing();

    response.type('text/xml');
